        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued July 16 at 3:04PM EDT until July 16 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM EDT, the public reported flooding in Oakland Township from
thunderstorms producing heavy rain over the past several hours.
Between 2 and 4 inches of rain have fallen. Storms have moved out of
the area, but additional rainfall amounts up to 0.5 inches remain
possible in the warned area over the next hour. Flash flooding is
already occurring.

HAZARD...Flash flooding caused by thunderstorms.

SOURCE...Public reported.

IMPACT...Flash flooding of small creeks and streams, urban areas,
highways, streets and underpasses as well as other poor
drainage and low-lying areas.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Romeo, Rochester, Rochester Hills, Auburn Hills, Lake Orion,
Washington, Leonard, Stoney Creek Metro Park and Lakeville.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
